==================================
User Manual For blutl
==================================

blutl: The util is used to set/get paramaters of bouffalolab WiFi driver.


COMMAND LIST:
	blutl wlanX version
	blutl wlanX temp
	blutl wlanX scan
    blutl wlanX scan_chan 
	blutl wlanX scan_ie  
	blutl wlanX country_code
	blutl wlanX mac_addr
	blutl wlanX rssi
	blutl wlanX read_efuse
	blutl wlanX status
    blutl wlanX event

COMMAND DESCRIPTION:
version
	This command is used to get the version of driver and FW.
	
	Usage:
		blutl wlan0 version

temp
	This command is used to get the IC temperature, unit 1 centigrade.

scan
    This command is used to start user defined scan 	
	Usage:
		blutl wlan0 scan [0/1]
		0： clear scan ie/channel setting
		1： start scan 

scan_chan
    This command is used to set scan channel list
	Usage:
		blutl wlanX scan_chan [chan1] [chan2] [chan3]

scan_ie
    This command is used to set scan ie		
	Usage:
		blutl wlan0 scan_ie [id] [len] [payload] 

country_code
    This command is used to get country code
	Usage:
		blutl wlan0 country_code

mac_addr
    This command is used to get mac address
	Usage:
		blutl wlan0 mac_addr
	
rssi	
    This command is used to get rssi value
	Usage:
		blutl wlan0 rssi
	
read_efuse	
    This command is used to get xtal/power offset/mac address in efuse
	Usage:
		blutl wlan0 read_efuse

status	
    This command is used to get wifi mode status, ap mode/sta mode/bridge mode
	Usage:
		blutl wlan0 status

event	
    This command is used to monitor event from driver
	Usage:
		blutl wlan0 event		